article.description: Liad Suez scored 18 points and Jennifer Hilgenberg added 16 to lead No. 24 Villanova over Fairfield 72-57 Tuesday night.
article.headline: Wildcats cruise behind Suez, Hilgenberg
article.linkText: Villanova tops Fairfield in first game in Top 25
article.story:
BRIDGEPORT, Conn. (AP) -- Liad Suez scored 18 points and Jennifer
Hilgenberg added 16 to lead Villanova (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today; No. 24 AP) over Fairfield 72-57
Tuesday night.

Villanova (2-0), which moved into The Associated Press Top 25
after beating Penn State in its opener Sunday, shot 57 percent from
the field and led nearly the entire game.

Jackie Adamshick had 10 points and six rebounds for Villanova,
which held a 35-23 rebounding advantage. Cathy Dash led Fairfield
(0-2) with 18 points and eight rebounds, and Sabra Wrice scored 15.

Villanova broke the game open early in the second half with an
11-2 run. Hilgenberg scored the final nine points of that run and
her 3-pointer moved the Wildcats in front 50-33.

Villanova took a 22-11 lead thanks to an 11-2 run midway through
the first half, capped by a 3-pointer by Liad Suez. But Fairfield
came back and pulled to 24-18 on a 3-pointer by Wrice, who scored
13 in the first half.

Kate Dessart Mager scored six points late in the half to help
the Wildcats take a 37-28 lead at halftime.
